This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with recognizing human actions in video sequences using visual appearance and motion dynamics. It also involves the use of Convolutional and Recurrent Neural Networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves the use of memory-augmented networks, which are a type of neural network architecture commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) tasks. 

Furthermore, the paper deals with video sequences, which fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves training the network using a straight-through estimator, which is a type of optimization technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
